Big news, Delaware: TODAY is the first day you can enroll, re-enroll, or change your health plan for 2024 through the Health Insurance Marketplace.

Check out my latest newsletter for steps you can take to make sure you’re covered for the upcoming year.

As the last Vietnam War veteran in the United States Senate, it’s always a privilege to serve our brave men and women in uniform and work to better understand the challenges they face. That’s why tomorrow, I will be heading to Dover for my annual Delaware Veterans Summit.

We have over 300 senior military officers waiting to be confirmed. It’s simply unacceptable. We cannot put our national security in jeopardy with so many vacant, critical positions. These distinguished individuals deserve to take their post, and it’s time we confirm them.

Great news, Delaware! Thanks to the Bipartisan Infrastructure Law, 
@USDOT
 is awarding $50 million for the Port of Wilmington’s Edgemoor terminal expansion.

This expansion project will improve safety, reduce emissions, and create some 19,000 more jobs — a win-win-win!

It was truly a joy to join 
@POTUS
 in Bear, Delaware to announce a major investment in the future of Amtrak!
 
This is going to make a real difference for the more than 750,000 Americans who ride along the Northeast Corridor each day.

November is Military Family Awareness Month.

Military families represent the best of America, and coming from a military family myself, I know the unique challenges they face. These families embody strength and sacrifice, and I’m proud to always have their backs in Congress.
WATCH LIVE: I’m on the Senate floor urging my colleagues to oppose a resolution that would undermine the American EV charging industry and send manufacturing jobs abroad.

Child care is increasingly unaffordable for working families all across our country. That’s why I’m joining my colleagues in urging congressional leadership to include robust funding for child care in any spending package that comes before the Senate.

Happy Veterans Day! 

One of the greatest things we can do to honor our veterans is to make sure they have well-deserved support when they return home. That’s why I recently held my annual Delaware Veterans Summit to discuss how we can support our veterans & their families.
Happy Diwali to everybody celebrating up and down Delaware! Martha and I wish you a bright and happy festival of lights.

Happy American Education Week! This week, and every week, we honor those who work in our nation’s schools – teachers, paraprofessionals, administrative staff, bus drivers, and everyone in between. 

Thank you for all that you do to set our students up for success!
